inlining markup?"),o.li("**Imports** \u2014 note which imports are used. If your edits remove the last usage of an import, delete that import line."),t.h2("Rules (must follow)"),t.paragraph("\u26A0\uFE0F **NEVER use inline `style={}`.** This is the single most common mistake and edits that introduce inline styles will be rejected. Always express styles as Tailwind utility classes (e.g. `bg-[#F7F7F7]`, `top-[600px]`, `w-[201px]`, `text-[#333]`) or by updating/composing existing CSS variables. Adding `style={{ backgroundColor: '...' }}` or `style={{ top: '...' }}` is **always wrong**, even if the element has no classes yet.");let r=t.ol();r.li("**No inline styles \u2014 use Tailwind classes or CSS variables.** For any new style, either add a Tailwind utility class (including arbitrary-value syntax like `bg-[#hex]`) or update the relevant CSS variable. Never add a `style={}` prop."),r.li("**Use existing abstractions.** Before hardcoding a color, spacing, or layout value, search for a CSS variable, Tailwind theme token, or design token that matches. Use the abstraction. Only hardcode a raw value if no match exists."),r.li("**Reuse existing components.** If a component or wrapper already encapsulates the element you need to change, modify that component\u2014do not bypass it by inlining its markup into a parent."),r.li("**Clean up dead code.** After every edit, check: are there now-unused imports, variables, or functions? Remove them."),r.li("**No raw sub-pixel values.** Values like `w-[85.5px]` or `left: 362px` are design-canvas measurements. Round to the nearest whole number or Tailwind spacing step. Prefer flex/grid/margin/padding over absolute positioning unless the element was already absolutely positioned."),r.li("**Choose the right positioning mode.** The design tool exports `position: absolute` for everything, but that is often wrong in code. Before applying positioning, reason about the element's role: use `fixed` for elements that stay on screen during scroll (